        "title": "feat(qqbot): add actionable setup error guidance",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Centralize QQBot setup/auth/network guidance in a plugin-owned helper.\n- Replace terse QQBot missing-config, token, and API network errors with actionable messages that include credentials guidance and docs links.\n- Preserve token retry visibility for token-fetch network failures and route QQBot API requests through the SSRF-guarded fetch path.\n\nCloses #65868.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/utils/setup-guidance.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `! rg 'await fetch\\(' extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/api-client.ts`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: QQBot setup, token, and network failures now provide actionable credential guidance, QQ Open Platform and docs links, account-aware named-account config paths, and retry-safe token-network wording instead of terse/raw messages.\n\nReal environment tested: Local full OpenClaw checkout on PR branch `codex/qqbot-actionable-errors-65868-20260618`, exercising the QQBot token manager and setup-guidance helper through the repository extension-messaging Vitest harness after the patch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/utils/setup-guidance.test.ts --reporter=verbose\ngit diff --check origin/main...HEAD\n! rg 'await fetch\\(' extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/api-client.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the focused QQBot run showed the changed guidance and retry behavior:\n\n```text\n✓ |extension-messaging| extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.test.ts > QQBot token manager > adds actionable guidance when the token response has no access token\n✓ |extension-messaging| extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.test.ts > QQBot token manager > keeps token network failures visible to the retry heuristic\n✓ |extension-messaging| extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.test.ts > QQBot token manager > passes the RFC2544 SSRF allowance to the token fetch (regression for #88984)\n✓ |extension-messaging| extensions/qqbot/src/engine/utils/setup-guidance.test.ts > QQBot setup guidance > points default-account setup errors to env vars and docs\n✓ |extension-messaging| extensions/qqbot/src/engine/utils/setup-guidance.test.ts > QQBot setup guidance > points named-account setup errors to account config keys\n✓ |extension-messaging| extensions/qqbot/src/engine/utils/setup-guidance.test.ts > QQBot setup guidance > keeps token and network failures actionable without dropping details\n\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  10 passed (10)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 4.29s\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The QQBot tests verify default-account guidance mentions env vars and docs, named-account guidance mentions account config keys, token/network guidance stays actionable without dropping raw details, token network failures still satisfy the existing retry heuristic, and token fetch keeps the SSRF allowance path. `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD` produced no output, and `rg` confirmed `extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/api-client.ts` no longer contains direct `await fetch(...)` calls.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live QQ Open Platform credential flow was not run in this environment; the focused QQBot runtime-unit paths above exercise the changed setup, token, network guidance, retry-signal, and SSRF-guard behavior without external credentials.\n",
